 Moses Kurgat has outfoxed other runners to win the Capricorn District Municipality’s CDM 4-in-One comrades marathon & two oceans qualifier 2018 held in Polokwane over the weekend. As African Times photo journalist Lebogang Makwela captured the moments, the 42.2 KM race attracted hopefuls from as far as Kenya.      WINNER: Kenyan sprinter Moses Kurgat won this year’s CDM 4-in-One comrades marathon & two oceans qualifier race held in Polokwane. Photos: Lebogang Makwela/ Visual Buzz SA. 